\section*{Problem 1}
\label{sec:orgcf01c6e}

To create the upper confidence limit, we use the formula,

\begin{equation}
\label{eq:org172ab58}
P(x<x_1|\mu)=1-\alpha
\end{equation}

and for central interval, we use

\begin{equation}
\label{eq:org012b271}
P(x<x_1|mu)=P(x>x_2)=\frac{(1-\alpha)}{2}
\end{equation}

We will take the central interval 68$\backslash$% and upper limit 90$\backslash$%.

\begin{description}
\item[{(a)}] Poisson Discrete random variable.
\end{description}
  \begin{equation}
\label{eq:org46ac0ef}
P(x|\mu) = \frac{\mu^x}{x!}e^{-\mu}
  \end{equation}

The plots are shown below.

